It may be obſerved, that it is exactly the ſame creative action
which produces the natural ſtructure, or any deviation from it;
for in caſes of deviation the action is either carried too far,
ceaſes too ſoon, or is diverted into uncommon channels. This
will explain the various kinds of monſtroſity from redundancy,
deficiency, or tranſpoſition of parts.
